main event: A witness observed a bright, white unidentified flying object over Tucson, Arizona on October 13, 1967.
interesting points: The object had no visible wings or other conventional aircraft features.
The object moved rapidly and changed direction suddenly without slowing down.
The witness attempted to photograph the object but the photos did not turn out well due to the bright light reflected from the object.
The object was observed for approximately 2 to 3 minutes before disappearing from view.
The witness reported the object was a bright white color.
photographs: yes, but they did not turn out well
